{"body": "@josevalim\n\ne-mails may be ONE use case, but I don't see them as the only or even the primary one.\n\nI'd love to know more about why `Thread.current` is considered harmful.  It seems to me that the request object is a pretty global (although temporal) kind of thing.\n\nAs for background stuff, why not make changes to the Queue API to pass the same values on to background jobs so they have the same context when they run?\n\nThis PR clearly does not represent a final solution, so let's discuss how we can alleviate the current pains in generating URLs.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/7650627", "created_at": "2012-08-10T17:05:48Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/7307#issuecomment-7650627", "updated_at": "2012-08-10T17:05:48Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 7307, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jacobo", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/dc893f8ae12045dc71048a0c6a56fc01?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F10fa5eb83300e5f592b9b35a0e07fc3f.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/received_events", "gravatar_id": "dc893f8ae12045dc71048a0c6a56fc01", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jacobo", "type": "User", "id": 10033, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jacobo/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5237fd63bd3543c15100bb0f"}, "id": 7650627, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/7307"}
